collections.name: The Little Icon of World Tobacco Day
collections.description:
This image takes me back to a day that became unexpectedly iconic in my life. I was just a child when this photo was taken during World Tobacco Day. It shows me holding a cigarette—not smoking it, as some might assume! The photograph was meant to symbolize the global fight against tobacco use and was even featured in a newspaper as part of an awareness campaign.

At the time, I had no idea that such a simple moment would hold so much meaning. Now, looking back, I see this picture as more than just an innocent memory; it’s a representation of how our actions, even unknowingly, can send a message. For me, it represents the responsibility we all have to educate and protect future generations from harmful habits like smoking.

This NFT is not just a snapshot of my childhood—it’s a reflection of my journey. As an adult, I look at this photo with both humor and purpose.

collections.name: NOHD EMS
collections.description: This artwork is a tribute to the brave individuals who form the heart and soul of the New Orleans Health Department Emergency Medical Services (NOHD EMS). It captures the essence of resilience, dedication, and unwavering community care. Inspired by my own experiences as a NOHD Paramedic, this piece symbolizes the unique balance of strength and compassion that defines EMS professionals. The fleur-de-lis represents the spirit of New Orleans, while the wings embody the lifesaving missions that soar into action every day.
